            "ignore": false,
            "order": 5,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "The rest of this article is organized as follows. Section II reviews related literature on the use of AI for ginger disease detection and management. Section III provides an overview of the common pests and diseases affecting ginger plants. Section IV presents the various methods of pest disease management under two categories: conventional methods and smart and precision methods. In Section  $V$ , the molecular methods and image processing techniques for pests and disease detection of ginger plants are presented. The use of AIoT for pests and disease management is discussed in Section VI. Section VII discusses the challenges in the adoption of AIoT and Section VIII points out the future directions. Finally, Section  $IX$  concludes this article.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
