            "order": 13,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "- 2) *Fusarium Yellows:* Fusarium yellows of ginger, caused by Fusarium oxysporum f. spp. zingiberi (Foz), is a devastating disease that has significantly reduced the quality and crop yield of ginger worldwide [39]. Infected plants exhibit leaf yellowing, wilting, and a rotten rhizome. Infected plant also produces shriveled tubers and sometimes brown ground tissue. Some of the symptoms appear to overlap with soft rot; however, experienced pathologists can distinguish this by symptom visualization.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
                        1292,
                        1860,
                        2298,
